This paper is about personalized conversation systems, which are a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for customizing language models, which involves training unique network structures for each user. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which could place it in the category of cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
